yt
==
version=0.2.0

AUTHOR
------
name="Tyler Cone"
email="herrflockig@gmail.com"

DESCRIPTION
-----------
yt is a python Youtube search client with a curses interface.

DEPENDENCIES
------------
mplayer
youtube-dl

USAGE
-----
yt (search query)
Example:
    yt black moth super rainbow
        *searches youtube for "black moth super rainbow"

Key Bindings:
    q            - quit
    j            - go down one result
    k            - go up one result
    ^d or pgdown - go down one page
    ^u or pgup   - go up one page
    /            - search
    enter        - play selected video
    o            - change ordering (relevance, view count, published date, rating)

ChangeLog
---------
todo

NEWS
----
version 0.1.0: made the basic interface
version 0.2.0: added autocomplete for searches in the main interface

INSTALL
-------
simply copy yt to a directory in your PATH and make it executable

Examples:
    install to the default directories
        cp yt.py /usr/bin/yt
        chmod +x /usr/bin/yt
    install to local directory
        cp yt.py ~/.local/bin/yt
        chmod +x ~/.local/bin/yt

COPYING / LICENSE
-----------------
yt is licensed under WTFPL. see LICENSE

BUGS
----
Crashes if you go past 1000 results. It's youtube's search api's limit.

CREDITS
-------
User interface and name largly inspired by (read ganked) https://github.com/rjw57/yt
